This paper deals with logic programming and answer set programming, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), programming languages (cs.PL), and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses preference handling and consistency restoration, which are topics relevant to the sub-field of description logic (cs.DL).
